parentClasses.name: Agent
parentClasses.annotation: Agent - vs:stable - Broad type that includes both organizations and people who play roles in the lifecycle of a resource. - Organization or person that acts or has the power to act. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Agent/json

parentClasses.name: AggregateDataProfile
parentClasses.annotation: Aggregate Data Profile - vs:stable - Resource containing summary statistical data. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/AggregateDataProfile/json

parentClasses.name: AlignmentMap
parentClasses.annotation: Alignment Map - vs:stable - Alignment maps provide the means for parties to assert sets of alignments between already existing entities created by themselves or other parties--e.g., a 3rd party mapping of a learning resource owned by one party to a credential owned by another; or, mapping a military occupational experience or Military Occupational Specialty (MOS code) as advanced standing to a course or credential. - An entity comprised of a set of alignment or mapping assertions between two existing entities such as mapping a certificate providing advanced standing to a degree. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/AlignmentMap/json

parentClasses.name: Assessment
parentClasses.annotation: Assessment - vs:stable - Direct, indirect, formative, and summative evaluation or estimation of the nature, ability, or quality of an entity, performance, or outcome of an action. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Assessment/json

parentClasses.name: Collection
parentClasses.annotation: Collection - vs:unstable - Aggregation of related resources. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Collection/json

parentClasses.name: CollectionComponent
parentClasses.annotation: Collection Component - vs:unstable - Resource that is a proxy for the entities contained in or referenced by an external Collection, Framework, or other such list, or for the list itself. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/CollectionComponent/json

parentClasses.name: CollectionMember
parentClasses.annotation: Collection Member - vs:unstable - Instances act as proxies or stand-ins for other resources in the context of a particular collection so that the relationships between them and the collection can be stated without implying that those relationships are true in other contexts. - Provides information about the membership of a resource in a Collection. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/CollectionMember/json

parentClasses.name: ComponentCondition
parentClasses.annotation: Component Condition - vs:stable - A ComponentCondition references a single RuleSet defining appropriate values fulfilling the condition. - Resource that describes what must be done to complete a PathwayComponent, or part thereof, as determined by the issuer of the Pathway. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/ComponentCondition/json

parentClasses.name: ConditionManifest
parentClasses.annotation: Condition Manifest - vs:stable - These conditions are intended to be referenced by external entities such as individual credentials in order to facilitate the process of their description and to reduce unnecessary duplication of data applicable across an array of entities. - Set of constraints, prerequisites, entry conditions, or requirements maintained at the organizational and/or sub-organizational level. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/ConditionManifest/json

parentClasses.name: Constraint
parentClasses.annotation: Constraint - vs:unstable - Resource that identifies the parameters defining a limitation or restriction applicable to candidate pathway components. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Constraint/json

parentClasses.name: ConstraintRule
parentClasses.annotation: Constraint Rule - vs:unstable - An instance of the Constraint Rule class is a deployable machine solution for executing pathway constraints using specifications such as XPath, JSONPath, JsonLogic, ShEx, SHACL, BPMN, XPDL and BPEL. - Abstract class of executable constraints. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/ConstraintRule/json

parentClasses.name: ContactPoint
parentClasses.annotation: Contact Point - vs:stable - For example, a public relations email address or phone number. - Means of contacting an organization or its representative. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/ContactPoint/json

parentClasses.name: CostManifest
parentClasses.annotation: Cost Manifest - vs:stable - Instances of these ceterms:CostManifest entities are intended to be referenced by other entities to augment the process of describing their costs. - Entity that describes a set of costs maintained at, and applicable across the organizational and/or sub-organizational level. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/CostManifest/json

parentClasses.name: CredentialAssertion
parentClasses.annotation: Credential Assertion - vs:stable - Representation of a credential awarded to a person. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/CredentialAssertion/json

parentClasses.name: CredentialFramework
parentClasses.annotation: Credential Framework - vs:stable - The class includes, but is not limited to, subclasses of specialized concept schemes describing industries, occupations, professions, learning contexts and jobs, as well as specialized subject concept schemes, assessment rubrics, proficiency scales, and competency frameworks. - Class of all structured sets of conceptual entities intentionally designed for use as value vocabulary terms for description and classification in the credentialing context. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/CredentialFramework/json

parentClasses.name: CredentialingAction
parentClasses.annotation: Credentialing Action - vs:stable - Since an instance of ceterms:CredentialingAction is a claim that a certain agent has taken the action being described, creation of such a ceterms:CredentialingAction should be reserved to the agent of that action. - Action taken by an agent affecting the status of an object entity. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/CredentialingAction/json

parentClasses.name: DurationProfile
parentClasses.annotation: Duration Profile - vs:stable - Temporal aspects include exact, minimum, and maximum timeframes of an activity. - Entity describing the temporal aspects of a resource. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/DurationProfile/json

parentClasses.name: FinancialAssistanceProfile
parentClasses.annotation: Financial Assistance Profile - vs:stable - Entity that describes financial assistance that is offered or available. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/FinancialAssistanceProfile/json

parentClasses.name: Industry
parentClasses.annotation: Industry - vs:unstable - Broad category of economic activities encompassing various sectors. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Industry/json

parentClasses.name: Job
parentClasses.annotation: Job - vs:stable - Job describes an abstraction or template that specific job postings or openings could be instances of. - Set of responsibilities based on work roles within an occupation as defined by an employer. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Job/json

parentClasses.name: LearningOpportunity
parentClasses.annotation: Learning Opportunity - vs:stable - Examples of learning opportunities include education and training programs and classes, courses of study, apprenticeship or work experience programs, or other structured experiences intended to serve as educational or training events. - Structured and unstructured learning and development opportunities based in direct experience, formal and informal study, observation, and involvement in discourse and practice. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/LearningOpportunity/json

parentClasses.name: MultiComponent
parentClasses.annotation: Multi Component - vs:unstable - Resource that is a proxy for multiple entities. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/MultiComponent/json

parentClasses.name: Occupation
parentClasses.annotation: Occupation - vs:stable - Profession, trade, or career field that may involve training and/or a formal qualification. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Occupation/json

parentClasses.name: Pathway
parentClasses.annotation: Pathway - vs:stable - Resource composed of a structured set of PathwayComponents defining points along a route to fulfillment of a goal or objective. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Pathway/json

parentClasses.name: PathwayComponent
parentClasses.annotation: Pathway Component - vs:stable - An instance of PathwayComponent may serve as the goal or destination node of a Pathway. - Resource that serves as a defined point along the route of a Pathway which describes an objective and its completion requirements through reference to one or more instances of ComponentCondition. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/PathwayComponent/json

parentClasses.name: Place
parentClasses.annotation: Place - vs:stable - Entity describing a physical location or geospatial area. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Place/json

parentClasses.name: ScheduledOffering
parentClasses.annotation: Scheduled Offering - vs:unstable - Provides data specific to a given scheduled offering; the Learning Opportunity (including Course and Learning Program) or Assessment being offered provides all data that is shared between different offerings. - Offering of a Learning Opportunity or Assessment with a schedule associated with a specified location or modality. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/ScheduledOffering/json

parentClasses.name: SupportService
parentClasses.annotation: Support Service - vs:unstable - Support services can be provided at any stage of an individual's education or career, and may be targeted towards people with or without direct affiliation with an organization. The goal of support services is to provide people with the assistance they need to achieve their full potential.  Examples of Support Services include career advice, job placement, childcare, transportation, tools, mentorship, counseling, and other forms of aid. - Resources and assistance that help people overcome barriers to succeed in their education and career goals. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/SupportService/json

parentClasses.name: Task
parentClasses.annotation: Task - vs:stable - Specific activity, typically related to performing a function or achieving a goal. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Task/json

parentClasses.name: TransferIntermediary
parentClasses.annotation: Transfer Intermediary - vs:unstable - Surrogate resource to which other resources are mapped in order to indicate their common transferability. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/TransferIntermediary/json

parentClasses.name: TransferValueProfile
parentClasses.annotation: Transfer Value Profile - vs:stable - Description of transfer value of a resource. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/TransferValueProfile/json

parentClasses.name: WorkRole
parentClasses.annotation: Work Role - vs:stable - Collection of tasks and competencies that embody a particular function in one or more jobs. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/WorkRole/json

parentClasses.name: QuantitativeValue
parentClasses.annotation: Quantitative Value - vs:stable - A point value or interval for product characteristics and other purposes. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/schema/QuantitativeValue/json

parentClasses.name: Competency
parentClasses.annotation: Competency - vs:stable - Competency is broadly defined to include assertions of academic, professional, occupational, vocational and life goals, outcomes, and standards, however labeled. - Measurable or observable knowledge, skill, or ability necessary to successful performance of a person. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdlasn/termhistory/ceasn/Competency/json

parentClasses.name: CriterionLevel
parentClasses.annotation: Criterion Level - vs:unstable - An individual component or specific element within a criterion that defines a particular aspect or standard for evaluation. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdlasn/termhistory/ceasn/CriterionLevel/json

parentClasses.name: Rubric
parentClasses.annotation: Rubric - vs:unstable - A structured and systematic evaluation tool used to assess performance, quality, and/or criteria. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdlasn/termhistory/ceasn/Rubric/json

parentClasses.name: RubricCriterion
parentClasses.annotation: Rubric Criterion - vs:unstable - Resource providing explicit criteria for ensuring specific and measurable evaluation. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdlasn/termhistory/ceasn/RubricCriterion/json

parentClasses.name: RubricLevel
parentClasses.annotation: Rubric Level - vs:unstable - Level or quality indicator used with Rubric Criteria. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdlasn/termhistory/ceasn/RubricLevel/json

parentClasses.name: Concept
parentClasses.annotation: Concept - vs:stable - Term in a controlled vocabulary. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdlasn/termhistory/skos/Concept/json

parentClasses.name: ConceptScheme
parentClasses.annotation: Concept Scheme - vs:stable - A controlled vocabulary. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdlasn/termhistory/skos/ConceptScheme/json

childClasses.name: AcademicCertificate
childClasses.annotation: Academic Certificate - vs:unstable - Formal education programs include academic, career, technical programs with defined completion requirements and often require approvals by provincial or federal government. - Credential awarded for successful completion of a formal education program, demonstrating requisite knowledge and skills. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/AcademicCertificate/json

childClasses.name: AccreditAction
childClasses.annotation: Accredit Action - vs:stable - Since an instance of ceterms:CredentialingAction is a claim that a certain agent has taken the action being described, creation of such a ceterms:CredentialingAction should be reserved to the agent of that action. - Action by an independent, neutral, and authoritative agent that certifies an entity as meeting a prescribed set of standards. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/AccreditAction/json

childClasses.name: AdvancedStandingAction
childClasses.annotation: Advanced Standing Action - vs:stable - Since an instance of ceterms:CredentialingAction is a claim that a certain agent has taken the action being described, creation of such a ceterms:CredentialingAction should be reserved to the agent of that action. - Claim by an agent asserting that the object credential of the action provides advanced standing for a credential under the asserting agent's authority. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/AdvancedStandingAction/json

childClasses.name: ApprenticeshipCertificate
childClasses.annotation: Apprentice Certificate - vs:stable - Credential awarded at the Apprentice level for successful completion of an apprenticeship program in industry trades and professions. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/ApprenticeshipCertificate/json

childClasses.name: ApproveAction
childClasses.annotation: Approve Action - vs:unstable - Since an instance of ceterms:CredentialingAction is a claim that a certain agent has taken the action being described, creation of such a ceterms:CredentialingAction should be reserved to the agent of that action. - Action by an independent, neutral, and authoritative agent that pronounces a favorable judgment of a credential. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/ApproveAction/json

childClasses.name: AssessmentComponent
childClasses.annotation: Assessment Component - vs:stable - Instances act as proxies or stand-ins for other resources in the context of a particular pathway so that relationships between them as components of that pathway can be stated without implying that the those relationships are true of the resources in other contexts. - Resource that identifies a direct, indirect, formative, and summative evaluation or estimation of the nature, ability, or quality of a resource, performance, or outcome of an action. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/AssessmentComponent/json

childClasses.name: AssessmentProfile
childClasses.annotation: Assessment Profile - vs:stable - Characteristics described include, but are not limited to, processes for assessment development, maintenance, selection and evaluation as well as assessment examples. - Entity that describes the key characteristics of an assessment for a credential. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/AssessmentProfile/json

childClasses.name: AssociateDegree
childClasses.annotation: Associate Degree - vs:stable - Equivalent to an award at UNESCO ISCED 2011, Level 5, and United States IPEDS Award Level 3. - College/university award for students typically completing the first two years of full-time postsecondary school education. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/AssociateDegree/json

childClasses.name: AssociateOfAppliedArtsDegree
childClasses.annotation: Associate of Applied Arts Degree - vs:unstable - Equivalent to an award at UNESCO ISCED 2011, Level 5, and United States IPEDS Award Level 3. - College/university award for students typically completing two years of full-time postsecondary school education in a technical, professional, or vocational program with an emphasis on direct employment in the arts and social sciences fields. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/AssociateOfAppliedArtsDegree/json

childClasses.name: AssociateOfAppliedScienceDegree
childClasses.annotation: Associate of Applied Science Degree - vs:unstable - Equivalent to an award at UNESCO ISCED 2011, Level 5, and United States IPEDS Award Level 3. - College/university award for students typically completing two years of full-time postsecondary school education in a technical, professional, or vocational program with an emphasis on direct employment in applied scientific and technological fields. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/AssociateOfAppliedScienceDegree/json

childClasses.name: AssociateOfArtsDegree
childClasses.annotation: Associate of Arts Degree - vs:unstable - Equivalent to an award at UNESCO ISCED 2011, Level 5, and United States IPEDS Award Level 3. - College/university award for students typically completing the first two years of full-time postsecondary school education with an emphasis in the liberal arts and sciences such as the humanities and social science fields. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/AssociateOfArtsDegree/json

childClasses.name: AssociateOfScienceDegree
childClasses.annotation: Associate of Science Degree - vs:unstable - Equivalent to an award at UNESCO ISCED 2011, Level 5, and United States IPEDS Award Level 3. - College/university award for students typically completing the first two years of full-time postsecondary school education with an emphasis in scientific and technical fields and professional fields of study. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/AssociateOfScienceDegree/json

childClasses.name: BachelorDegree
childClasses.annotation: Bachelor's Degree - vs:stable - Equivalent to an award at UNESCO ISCED 2011, Level 6, and United States IPEDS Award Level 5. - College/university award for students typically completing three to five years of education where course work and activities advance skills beyond those of the first one to two years of college/university study. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/BachelorDegree/json

childClasses.name: BachelorOfArtsDegree
childClasses.annotation: Bachelor of Arts Degree - vs:unstable - Equivalent to an award at UNESCO ISCED 2011, Level 6, and United States IPEDS Award Level 5. - College/university award for students typically completing three to five years of education where course work and activities advance skills beyond those of the first one to two years of college/university study, with an emphasis in the liberal arts and sciences such as the humanities and social science fields. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/BachelorOfArtsDegree/json

childClasses.name: BachelorOfScienceDegree
childClasses.annotation: Bachelor of Science Degree - vs:unstable - Equivalent to an award at UNESCO ISCED 2011, Level 6, and United States IPEDS Award Level 5. - College/university award for students typically completing three to five years of education where course work and activities advance skills beyond those of the first one to two years of college/university study, with an emphasis in scientific and technical fields and professional fields of study. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/BachelorOfScienceDegree/json

childClasses.name: Badge
childClasses.annotation: Badge - vs:stable - Recognition designed to be displayed as a marker of accomplishment, activity, achievement, skill, interest, association, or identity. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Badge/json

childClasses.name: BasicComponent
childClasses.annotation: Basic Component - vs:stable - Instances act as proxies or stand-ins for other resources in the context of a particular pathway so that relationships between them as components of that pathway can be stated without implying that the those relationships are true of the resources in other contexts. - Resource that identifies a resource not otherwise covered by the enumerated PathwayComponent subclasses. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/BasicComponent/json

childClasses.name: BasicTechnicalCertificate
childClasses.annotation: Basic Technical Certificate - vs:unstable - Typically equivalent to a United States IPEDS level 1a that specifies postsecondary certificates of less than 300 clock hours, or less than 9 semester or trimester credit hours, or less than 13 quarter credit hours. - Credential awarded at a postsecondary level for successful completion of a formal education program that is completed within one semester, demonstrating competencies within a specific occupational area, indicating job readiness. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/BasicTechnicalCertificate/json

childClasses.name: Certificate
childClasses.annotation: Certificate - vs:stable - Distinct from degrees of higher education and typically non-renewable. For degrees of higher education use an appropriate type from the Degree hierarchy. - Credential which designates participation in, completion of, or demonstration of requisite knowledge and skills for a formal academic or training program, an occupation, or non-formal learning. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Certificate/json

childClasses.name: CertificateOfCompletion
childClasses.annotation: Certificate of Completion - vs:stable - A record of the activity may or may not exist, and the credential may or may not be designed as preparation for another resource such as a credential, assessment, or learning opportunity. - Credential that acknowledges completion of an assignment, training or other activity. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/CertificateOfCompletion/json

childClasses.name: CertificateOfParticipation
childClasses.annotation: Certificate of Participation - vs:unstable - These certificates do not imply completion, or mastery of specific skills, or that a grade has been awarded, but recognize the individual's active participation with an activity. A record of the activity may or may not exist, and the credential may or may not be designed as preparation for another resource such as a credential, assessment, or learning opportunity. - Credential that acknowledges attendance and/or engagement in an activity. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/CertificateOfParticipation/json

childClasses.name: Certification
childClasses.annotation: Certification - vs:stable - Certifications can typically be revoked if not renewed, for a violation of a code of ethics (if applicable) or proven incompetence after due process. Description of revocation criteria for a specific Certification should be defined using Revocation Profile. - Time-limited, revocable, renewable credential awarded by an authoritative body for demonstrating the knowledge, skills, and abilities to perform specific tasks or an occupation. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Certification/json

childClasses.name: CocurricularComponent
childClasses.annotation: Cocurricular Component - vs:stable - Instances act as proxies or stand-ins for other resources in the context of a particular pathway so that relationships between them as components of that pathway can be stated without implying that the those relationships are true of the resources in other contexts. - Resource that identifies an activity, program, or informal learning experience such as a civic or service activity that supplements and complements the curriculum. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/CocurricularComponent/json

childClasses.name: CompetencyComponent
childClasses.annotation: Competency Component - vs:stable - Competency is broadly defined to include assertions of academic, professional, occupational, vocational and life goals, outcomes, and standards, however labeled. Instances act as proxies or stand-ins for other resources in the context of a particular pathway so that relationships between them as components of that pathway can be stated without implying that the those relationships are true of the resources in other contexts. - Resource that identifies a measurable or observable knowledge, skill, or ability necessary to successful performance of a person in a given context. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/CompetencyComponent/json

childClasses.name: ConditionProfile
childClasses.annotation: Condition Profile - vs:stable - Constraints exist with credentials, learning opportunities, assessments and other entites to which they are subject during their lifecycles. - Entity describing a constraint, prerequisite, entry condition, or requirement. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/ConditionProfile/json

childClasses.name: CostProfile
childClasses.annotation: Cost Profile - vs:stable - Entity that describes direct costs one would incur if one were to pursue a credential, assessment, learning opportunity, or aspects thereof. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/CostProfile/json

childClasses.name: Course
childClasses.annotation: Course - vs:stable - Course is distinct from Program, which aggregates several courses. - Single structured sequence of one or more educational activities that aims to develop a prescribed set of competencies of learners. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Course/json

childClasses.name: CourseComponent
childClasses.annotation: Course Component - vs:stable - Instances act as proxies or stand-ins for other resources in the context of a particular pathway so that relationships between them as components of that pathway can be stated without implying that the those relationships are true of the resources in other contexts. - Resource that identifies a structured sequence of one or more learning activities that aims to develop a prescribed set of knowledge, skill, or ability of learners. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/CourseComponent/json

childClasses.name: Credential
childClasses.annotation: Credential - vs:stable - The ceterms:Credential class is broadly defined to encompass credentials used across domains and communities of practice. The class should be used only when speaking of credentials in general. Subclasses of ceterms:Credential as defined by Credential Engine (or other communities) should be used when referencing specific types of credentials. - Qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity typically used to indicate suitability. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Credential/json

childClasses.name: CredentialAlignmentObject
childClasses.annotation: Credential Alignment Object - vs:stable - Entity describing an affiliation or association between an entity such as a credential, learning opportunity or assessment and another entity in a structured framework such as a concept scheme, enumerated list, or competency framework. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/CredentialAlignmentObject/json

childClasses.name: CredentialComponent
childClasses.annotation: Credential Component - vs:stable - The ceterms:Credential class is broadly defined to encompass credentials used across domains and communities of practice. Subclasses of ceterms:Credential as defined by Credential Engine (or other communities) should be referenced. Instances act as proxies or stand-ins for other resources in the context of a particular pathway so that relationships between them as components of that pathway can be stated without implying that the those relationships are true of the resources in other contexts. - Resource that identifies another resource that describes qualification, achievement, personal or organizational quality, or aspect of an identity typically used to indicate suitability. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/CredentialComponent/json

childClasses.name: CredentialOrganization
childClasses.annotation: Credential Organization - vs:stable - Organization that plays one or more key roles in the lifecycle of a credential. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/CredentialOrganization/json

childClasses.name: CredentialPerson
childClasses.annotation: CredentialPerson - vs:stable - The ceterms:CredentialPerson class should be used to describe persons directly engaged as primary agent in credentialing actions such as approving, offering, recognizing, renewing and revoking credentials and should not include persons merely affiliated with, or employed by organizations that perform such actions. - Person who plays a role as primary agent in a credentialing action. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/CredentialPerson/json

childClasses.name: Degree
childClasses.annotation: Degree - vs:stable - Academic credential conferred upon completion of a program or course of study, typically over multiple years at a college or university. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Degree/json

childClasses.name: DigitalBadge
childClasses.annotation: Digital Badge - vs:stable - Badge offered in digital form. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/DigitalBadge/json

childClasses.name: Diploma
childClasses.annotation: Diploma - vs:stable - Credential awarded by educational institutions for successful completion of a course of study or its equivalent. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Diploma/json

childClasses.name: DoctoralDegree
childClasses.annotation: Doctoral Degree - vs:stable - Equivalent to UNESCO ISCED, Level 8 and United States IPEDS Award Levels 17, 18, and 19. - Highest credential award for students who have completed both a bachelor's degree and a master's degree or their equivalent as well as independent research and/or a significant project or paper. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/DoctoralDegree/json

childClasses.name: EarningsProfile
childClasses.annotation: Earnings Profile - vs:stable - Entity that describes earning and related statistical information for a given credential. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/EarningsProfile/json

childClasses.name: EmploymentOutcomeProfile
childClasses.annotation: Employment Outcome Profile - vs:stable - Entity that describes employment outcomes and related statistical information for a given credential. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/EmploymentOutcomeProfile/json

childClasses.name: ExtracurricularComponent
childClasses.annotation: Extracurricular Component - vs:stable - Instances act as proxies or stand-ins for other resources in the context of a particular pathway so that relationships between them as components of that pathway can be stated without implying that the those relationships are true of the resources in other contexts. - Resource that identifies an activity, program, or informal learning experience that may be offered or provided by a school, college, or other organization that is not connected to a curriculum. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/ExtracurricularComponent/json

childClasses.name: GeneralEducationDevelopment
childClasses.annotation: General Education Development (GED) - vs:stable - Equivalent to a secondary school diploma, based on passing a state- or province-selected examination such as GED, HiSET, or TASC; or to an award at UNESCO ISCED 2011 Levels 2 or 3. - Credential awarded by examination that demonstrates that an individual has acquired secondary school-level academic skills. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/GeneralEducationDevelopment/json

childClasses.name: GeneralEducationLevel1Certificate
childClasses.annotation: General Education Level 1 Certificate - vs:unstable - Can lead to a General Education Certificate Level 2 or a degree. Equivalent to a United States IPEDS Award Level 1b that specifies postsecondary certificates of 300-899 clock hours, or 9-29 semester or trimester credit hours, or 13-44 quarter credit hours. - Credential award at a postsecondary level for successful completion of general education courses that cover a broad range of foundational academic skills and takes less than 1 year. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/GeneralEducationLevel1Certificate/json

childClasses.name: GeneralEducationLevel2Certificate
childClasses.annotation: General Education Level 2 Certificate - vs:unstable - Can lead to a degree. Equivalent to a United States IPEDS Award Level 2 that specifies postsecondary certificates of at least 900 but less than 1,800 clock hours, or at least 30 but less than 60 semester or trimester credit hours, or at least 45 but less than 90 quarter credit hours. - Credential award at a postsecondary level for successful completion of general education courses that takes at least 1 year that cover a broad range of foundational academic skills and takes less than 2 years to complete. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/GeneralEducationLevel2Certificate/json

childClasses.name: GeoCoordinates
childClasses.annotation: Geographic Coordinates - vs:stable - Geographic coordinates of a place or event including latitude and longitude as well as other locational information. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/GeoCoordinates/json

childClasses.name: HigherEducationLevel1Certificate
childClasses.annotation: Higher Education Level 1 Certificate - vs:unstable - Typically equivalent to 60 ECTS Credits at Level 5 in the European Qualifications Framework. - Credential awarded at the postsecondary level for successful completion of a formal higher education program that takes about one year in a specific subject. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/HigherEducationLevel1Certificate/json

childClasses.name: HigherEducationLevel2Certificate
childClasses.annotation: Higher Education Level 2 Certificate - vs:unstable - Typically equivalent to 120 ECTS Credits at Level 5 in the European Qualifications Framework and the Short Cycle in the Qualifications Framework of the European Higher Education Area. - Credential awarded at the postsecondary level for successful completion of a formal higher education program that takes about two years in a specific subject. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/HigherEducationLevel2Certificate/json

childClasses.name: HoldersProfile
childClasses.annotation: Holders Profile - vs:stable - Entity describing the count and related statistical information of holders of a given credential. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/HoldersProfile/json

childClasses.name: IdentifierValue
childClasses.annotation: Identifier Value - vs:stable - Means of identifying a resource, typically consisting of an alphanumeric token and a context or scheme from which that token originates. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/IdentifierValue/json

childClasses.name: IndustryClassification
childClasses.annotation: Industry Classification - vs:stable - Class of of concept schemes defining industries such as NAICS in the U.S. and ESCO in the European Union. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/IndustryClassification/json

childClasses.name: InstructionalProgramClassification
childClasses.annotation: Instructional Program Classification - vs:stable - Class of concept schemes defining instructional program types such as the CIP codes in the U.S. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/InstructionalProgramClassification/json

childClasses.name: JobComponent
childClasses.annotation: Job Component - vs:stable - Instances act as proxies or stand-ins for other resources in the context of a particular pathway so that relationships between them as components of that pathway can be stated without implying that the those relationships are true of the resources in other contexts. - Resource that identifies a work position, employment, or occupation. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/JobComponent/json

childClasses.name: JourneymanCertificate
childClasses.annotation: Journeyman Certificate - vs:stable - Credential awarded at the Journeyman level for successful completion of an apprenticeship program in industry trades and professions. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/JourneymanCertificate/json

childClasses.name: JurisdictionProfile
childClasses.annotation: Jurisdiction Profile - vs:stable - Geo-political information about applicable geographic areas and their exceptions. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/JurisdictionProfile/json

childClasses.name: LearningOpportunityProfile
childClasses.annotation: Learning Opportunity Profile - vs:stable - Opportunities include formal and informal educational training programs and classes, apprenticeship or work experience programs, or other structured or unstructured experiences that serve as educational or training activities. - Entity describing an educational or training opportunity. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/LearningOpportunityProfile/json

childClasses.name: LearningProgram
childClasses.annotation: Learning Program - vs:unstable - Set of learning opportunities that leads to an outcome, usually a credential like a degree or certificate. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/LearningProgram/json

childClasses.name: LearningResource
childClasses.annotation: Learning Resource - vs:stable - Entity that is used as part of an learning activity (e.g. a textbook) or that describes (e.g. a lesson plan) or records the educational activity (e.g. an audio- or video-recording of a lesson). - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/LearningResource/json

childClasses.name: License
childClasses.annotation: License - vs:stable - Credential awarded by a government agency or other authorized organization that constitutes legal authority to do a specific job and/or utilize a specific item, system or infrastructure and are typically earned through some combination of degree or certificate attainment, certifications, assessments, work experience, and/or fees, and are time-limited and must be renewed periodically. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/License/json

childClasses.name: MasterCertificate
childClasses.annotation: Master Trade Certificate - vs:stable - Credential awarded at the Master level for demonstration of the highest level of skills and performance in industry trades and professions. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/MasterCertificate/json

childClasses.name: MasterDegree
childClasses.annotation: Master's Degree - vs:stable - Equivalent to an award at UNESCO ISCED 2011, Level 7, and United States IPEDS Award Level 7. - Credential awarded for a graduate level course of study where course work and activities advance skills beyond those of the bachelor's degree or its equivalent. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/MasterDegree/json

childClasses.name: MasterOfArtsDegree
childClasses.annotation: Master of Arts Degree - vs:unstable - Equivalent to an award at UNESCO ISCED 2011, Level 7, and United States IPEDS Award Level 7. - Credential awarded for a graduate level course of study where course work and activities advance skills beyond those of the bachelor's degree or its equivalent, with an emphasis in the liberal arts and sciences such as the humanities and social science fields. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/MasterOfArtsDegree/json

childClasses.name: MasterOfScienceDegree
childClasses.annotation: Master of Science Degree - vs:unstable - Equivalent to an award at UNESCO ISCED 2011, Level 7, and United States IPEDS Award Level 7. - Credential awarded for a graduate level course of study where course work and activities advance skills beyond those of the bachelor's degree or its equivalent, with an emphasis in scientific and technical fields and professional fields of study. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/MasterOfScienceDegree/json

childClasses.name: MicroCredential
childClasses.annotation: Micro-Credential - vs:stable - Credential that addresses a subset of field-specific knowledge, skills, or competencies; often developmental with relationships to other micro-credentials and field credentials. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/MicroCredential/json

childClasses.name: OccupationClassification
childClasses.annotation: Occupation Classification - vs:stable - Class of concept schemes identifying occupations such as the Standard Occupational Classification (SOC) system in the U.S. and the European Skills/Competences, Qualifications and Occupations (ESCO). - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/OccupationClassification/json

childClasses.name: OfferAction
childClasses.annotation: Offer Action - vs:stable - Since an instance of ceterms:CredentialingAction is a claim that a certain agent has taken the action being described, creation of such a ceterms:CredentialingAction should be reserved to the agent of that action. - Action by an authoritative agent offering access to a entity such as a credential, learning opportunity or assessment. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/OfferAction/json

childClasses.name: OpenBadge
childClasses.annotation: Open Badge - vs:stable - Visual symbol containing verifiable claims in accordance with the Open Badges specification and delivered digitally. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/OpenBadge/json

childClasses.name: Organization
childClasses.annotation: Organization - vs:stable - An entity such as an association, company, corporation, club, co-operative, labor union etc. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/Organization/json

childClasses.name: PathwaySet
childClasses.annotation: Pathway Set - vs:stable - A roadmap of multiple related pathways that lead to one or more destinations. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/PathwaySet/json

childClasses.name: PostalAddress
childClasses.annotation: Postal Address - vs:stable - Entity describing a mailing address. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/PostalAddress/json

childClasses.name: PostBaccalaureateCertificate
childClasses.annotation: Post-Baccalaureate Certificate - vs:unstable - This may include certificates that are for specialties within an occupational field or occupational program of study. Equivalent to a United States IPEDS Award Level 6. - Credential award that requires completion of an organized program of study at a level beyond that of a bachelor's degree, which is designed for persons who have completed a baccalaureate degree but does not meet the requirements of a master's degree. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/PostBaccalaureateCertificate/json

childClasses.name: PostMasterCertificate
childClasses.annotation: Post-Master Certificate - vs:unstable - This may include certificates that are for specialties within an occupational field or occupational program of study and can include post-doctoral first professional certificates such as healthcare and law. Equivalent to a United States IPEDS Award Level 7 or 17, 18, and 19. - Credential award that requires completion of an organized program of study beyond that of a master's degree, which is designed for persons who have completed a master's degree but does not meet the requirements of a doctor's degree. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/PostMasterCertificate/json

childClasses.name: PreApprenticeshipCertificate
childClasses.annotation: Pre-Apprenticeship Certificate - vs:unstable - Credential awarded to indicate readiness for an apprentice-level program. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/PreApprenticeshipCertificate/json

childClasses.name: ProcessProfile
childClasses.annotation: Process Profile - vs:stable - Entity describing the type, nature, and other relevant information about a process related to a credential. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/ProcessProfile/json

childClasses.name: ProfessionalCertificate
childClasses.annotation: Professional Certificate - vs:unstable - These certificates validate competency in tasks, tools, software, or procedures within a particular industry and are often awarded by training centers, career and technical education, industry organizations, or businesses. - Credential awarded for demonstrating competencies in a profession or particular occupational field, including job readiness. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/ProfessionalCertificate/json

childClasses.name: ProfessionalDoctorate
childClasses.annotation: Professional Doctorate - vs:stable - Equivalent to UNESCO ISCED, Level 8 and United States IPEDS Award Level 18. - Doctoral degree conferred upon completion of a program providing the knowledge and skills for the recognition, credential, or license required for professional practice. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/ProfessionalDoctorate/json

childClasses.name: ProficiencyCertificate
childClasses.annotation: Proficiency Certificate - vs:unstable - Examples of specific areas include language, typing, music, and dance. - Credential awarded after assessment of skills in a specific area defined by a recognized body of experts, without regard for how the skills were learned. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/ProficiencyCertificate/json

childClasses.name: QACredentialOrganization
childClasses.annotation: QA Credential Organization - vs:stable - Quality assurance organization that plays one or more key roles in the lifecycle of a credential, learning program, or assessment. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/QACredentialOrganization/json

childClasses.name: QualityAssuranceCredential
childClasses.annotation: Quality Assurance Credential - vs:stable - Credential assuring that an organization, program, or awarded credential meets prescribed requirements and may include development and administration of qualifying examinations. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/QualityAssuranceCredential/json

childClasses.name: RecognizeAction
childClasses.annotation: Recognize Action - vs:stable - Since an instance of ceterms:CredentialingAction is a claim that a certain agent has taken the action being described, creation of such a ceterms:CredentialingAction should be reserved to the agent of that action. - Action by an independent, neutral, and authoritative agent acknowledging the validity of a resource. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/RecognizeAction/json

childClasses.name: RegistrationAction
childClasses.annotation: Registration Action - vs:unstable - Action by an independent, neutral, and authoritative agent that registers a resource that has been vetted, approved, and validated to meet specific criteria. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/RegistrationAction/json

childClasses.name: RegulateAction
childClasses.annotation: Regulate Action - vs:unstable - Since an instance of ceterms:CredentialingAction is a claim that a certain agent has taken the action being described, creation of such a ceterms:CredentialingAction should be reserved to the agent of that action. - Action by an independent, neutral, and authoritative agent enforcing the legal requirements of a resource. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/RegulateAction/json

childClasses.name: RenewAction
childClasses.annotation: Renew Action - vs:stable - Since an instance of ceterms:CredentialingAction is a claim that a certain agent has taken the action being described, creation of such a ceterms:CredentialingAction should be reserved to the agent of that action. - Action by an agent renewing an existing credential assertion. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/RenewAction/json

childClasses.name: ResearchDoctorate
childClasses.annotation: Research Doctorate - vs:stable - Equivalent to UNESCO ISCED, Level 8 and United States IPEDS Award Level 17. - Doctoral degree conferred for advanced work beyond the master level, including the preparation and defense of a thesis or dissertation based on original research, or the planning and execution of an original project demonstrating substantial artistic or scholarly achievement. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/ResearchDoctorate/json

childClasses.name: RevocationProfile
childClasses.annotation: Revocation Profile - vs:stable - Entity describing conditions and methods by which a credential can be removed from a holder. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/RevocationProfile/json

childClasses.name: RevokeAction
childClasses.annotation: Revoke Action - vs:stable - Since an instance of ceterms:CredentialingAction is a claim that a certain agent has taken the action being described, creation of such a ceterms:CredentialingAction should be reserved to the agent of that action. - Action by an agent removing an awarded credential (credential assertion) from the credential holder based on violations or failure of the holder to renew. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/RevokeAction/json

childClasses.name: RightsAction
childClasses.annotation: Rights Action - vs:stable - Since an instance of ceterms:CredentialingAction is a claim that a certain agent has taken the action being described, creation of such a ceterms:CredentialingAction should be reserved to the agent of that action. - Action asserting legal rights by an agent to possess, defend, transfer, license, and grant conditional access to a credential, learning opportunity, or assessment. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/RightsAction/json

childClasses.name: SecondaryEducationCertificate
childClasses.annotation: Secondary Education Certificate - vs:unstable - Credential for successful completion of a formal secondary-level education program that is less than a diploma and does not indicate completion of secondary education graduation requirements. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/SecondaryEducationCertificate/json

childClasses.name: SecondarySchoolDiploma
childClasses.annotation: Secondary School Diploma - vs:stable - Equivalent to an award at UNESCO ISCED 2011 Levels 2 or 3. - Diploma awarded by secondary education institutions for successful completion of a secondary school program of study. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/SecondarySchoolDiploma/json

childClasses.name: SpecialistDegree
childClasses.annotation: Specialist Degree - vs:unstable - Equivalent to UNESCO ISCED, Level 8, and United States IPEDS Award Level 8. - Credential awarded for a graduate level course of study where course work and activities advance skills beyond those of the master’s degree and less than a doctoral degree and provide specific preparation for advanced careers in a specialist field. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/SpecialistDegree/json

childClasses.name: TechnicalLevel1Certificate
childClasses.annotation: Technical Level 1 Certificate - vs:unstable - Can lead to a Technical Certificate Level 2 or a degree. Equivalent to a United States IPEDS Award Level 1b that specifies postsecondary certificates of 300-899 clock hours, or 9-29 semester or trimester credit hours, or 13-44 quarter credit hours. - Credential award at a postsecondary level for successful completion of a formal education program that is more than one semester and less than 1 year, demonstrating competencies within a specific subject area or an occupational area indicating job readiness. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/TechnicalLevel1Certificate/json

childClasses.name: TechnicalLevel2Certificate
childClasses.annotation: Technical Level 2 Certificate - vs:unstable - Can lead to a degree. Equivalent to a United States IPEDS Award Level 2 that specifies postsecondary certificates of at least 900 but less than 1,800 clock hours, or at least 30 but less than 60 semester or trimester credit hours, or at least 45 but less than 90 quarter credit hours. - Credential award at a postsecondary level for successful completion of a formal education program that is at least 1 year but less than 2 years, demonstrating competencies within a specific subject area or in an occupational area indicating job readiness. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/TechnicalLevel2Certificate/json

childClasses.name: TechnicalLevel3Certificate
childClasses.annotation: Technical Level 3 Certificate - vs:unstable - Can lead to a degree. Equivalent to a United States IPEDS Award Level 4 that specifies certificates of 1,800 or more clock hours, or 60 or more semester or trimester credit hours, or 90 or more quarter credit hours. - Credential award at a postsecondary level for successful completion of a formal education program that is at least 2 years but less than 4 years, demonstrating competencies within specific occupational areas indicating job readiness. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/TechnicalLevel3Certificate/json

childClasses.name: ValueProfile
childClasses.annotation: Value Profile - vs:stable - A description of value awarded for, required by, or otherwise related to the resource. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/ValueProfile/json

childClasses.name: VerificationServiceProfile
childClasses.annotation: Verification Service Profile - vs:stable - Includes, but is not limited to, verification of whether quality assurance credentials have been issued for organizations, learning opportunities, and assessments. - Entity describing the means by which someone can verify whether a credential has been attained. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/VerificationServiceProfile/json

childClasses.name: WorkBasedLearningCertificate
childClasses.annotation: Work-Based Learning Certificate - vs:unstable - Work-based learning includes many types of skills training that are occupation specific including, but not limited to apprenticeships. - Credential awarded for work-based learning and earn-and-learn models that meet standards and are applicable to industry, trades, occupations, and professions. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/WorkBasedLearningCertificate/json

childClasses.name: WorkExperienceComponent
childClasses.annotation: Work Experience Component - vs:stable - Instances act as proxies or stand-ins for other resources in the context of a particular pathway so that relationships between them as components of that pathway can be stated without implying that the those relationships are true of the resources in other contexts. - Resource describing an activity or training through which a person gains job experience. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/WorkExperienceComponent/json

childClasses.name: WorkforceDemandAction
childClasses.annotation: Workforce Demand Action - vs:unstable - Action taken by an agent asserting that the resource being described has a workforce demand level worthy of note. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/WorkforceDemandAction/json

childClasses.name: ProgressionLevel
childClasses.annotation: Progression Level - vs:stable - Identifiable point along a developmental progression of competence, achievement or temporal position. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdlasn/termhistory/asn/ProgressionLevel/json

childClasses.name: ProgressionModel
childClasses.annotation: Progression Model - vs:stable - Model of identifiable points along a developmental progression including increasing levels of competence, achievement or temporal position (e.g., "Second Quarter"). - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdlasn/termhistory/asn/ProgressionModel/json

childClasses.name: CompetencyFramework
childClasses.annotation: Competency Framework - vs:stable - A competency framework serves a container object for a set of competencies. - Entity comprised of a logically related set of competencies. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdlasn/termhistory/ceasn/CompetencyFramework/json

childClasses.name: ProficiencyScale
childClasses.annotation: Proficiency Scale - vs:stable - Proficiency scales define levels of performance (what a person does) as distinct from knowledge of specific information (what a person knows) and outline tasks a person can manage and the skills necessary to progressively accomplish explicit competencies at increasing levels of complexity. Proficiency scales: (1) assist in making judgments about the kinds of tasks related to a competency that a person is able to perform; and (2) to compare the abilities of different persons with regard to achievement of those competencies at different levels. - The class of structured profiles describing discrete levels of expertise and performance mastery. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdlasn/termhistory/ceasn/ProficiencyScale/json

objectProperties.name: abilityEmbodied
objectProperties.annotation: Ability Embodied - vs:stable - Enduring attributes of the individual that influence performance are embodied either directly or indirectly in this resource. - Usage Node: The abilityEmbodied property may referenced a defined ability in an ontology such as O*NET or an existing competency defined in a competency framework. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceasn/abilityEmbodied/json

objectProperties.name: comment
objectProperties.annotation: Comment - vs:stable - Supplemental text provided by the promulgating body that clarifies the nature, scope or use of this resource. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceasn/comment/json

objectProperties.name: knowledgeEmbodied
objectProperties.annotation: Knowledge Embodied - vs:stable - Body of information embodied either directly or indirectly in this resource. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceasn/knowledgeEmbodied/json

objectProperties.name: listID
objectProperties.annotation: List ID - vs:stable - An alphanumeric string indicating the relative position of a resource in an ordered list of resources such as "A", "B", or "a", "b", or "I", "II", or "1", "2". - Usage Node: Punctuation accompanying alphanumeric strings should not be included. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceasn/listID/json

objectProperties.name: skillEmbodied
objectProperties.annotation: Skill Embodied - vs:stable - Ability to apply knowledge and use know-how to complete tasks and solve problems including types or categories of developed proficiency or dexterity in mental operations and physical processes is embodied either directly or indirectly in this resource. - Usage Node: The skillEmbodied property may reference a defined skill in an ontology such as O*NET or an existing competency defined in a competency framework. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceasn/skillEmbodied/json

objectProperties.name: accommodationType
objectProperties.annotation: Accommodation Type - vs:unstable - Type of modification to facilitate equal access for people to a physical location, resource, or service. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/accommodationType/json

objectProperties.name: accreditedIn
objectProperties.annotation: Accredited In - vs:stable - Region or political jurisdiction such as a state, province or locale in which the credential, learning opportunity or assessment is accredited. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/accreditedIn/json

objectProperties.name: actionStatusType
objectProperties.annotation: Action Status Type - vs:stable - Entity describing the current disposition or standing of an action; select from an existing enumeration of such types. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/actionStatusType/json

objectProperties.name: address
objectProperties.annotation: Address - vs:stable - Particulars describing the location of the place. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/address/json

objectProperties.name: addressCountry
objectProperties.annotation: Address Country - vs:stable - Nation with its own government and occupying a particular territory identified by the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/addressCountry/json

objectProperties.name: addressLocality
objectProperties.annotation: Address Locality - vs:stable - Town, city, or village in which a particular location is situtated. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/addressLocality/json

objectProperties.name: addressRegion
objectProperties.annotation: Address Region - vs:stable - State or province in which a particular location is situated. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/addressRegion/json

objectProperties.name: administrationProcess
objectProperties.annotation: Administration Process - vs:stable - Description of a process by which a resource is administered. - Usage Node: For assessments and rubrics, this can be used to indicate the scoring algorithm. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/administrationProcess/json

objectProperties.name: agentPurpose
objectProperties.annotation: Agent Purpose - vs:stable - Organization's primary purpose as found on an "about" page of a website. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/agentPurpose/json

objectProperties.name: agentPurposeDescription
objectProperties.annotation: Agent Purpose Description - vs:stable - Short, key phrases describing the primary purpose of an organization as might be derived from the "about" page of it's website. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/agentPurposeDescription/json

objectProperties.name: agentSectorType
objectProperties.annotation: Agent Sector Type - vs:stable - Type of sociological, economic, or political subdivision served by an organization; select from an existing enumeration of such types. - Usage Node: Recommended best practice for credentials in the Credential Engine Registry is to use concepts from the ceterms:AgentSector vocabulary. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/agentSectorType/json

objectProperties.name: agentType
objectProperties.annotation: Agent Type - vs:stable - Type of organization such as educational institution, credentialing organization or quality assurance body; select from an existing enumeration of such types. - Usage Node: Best practice for developing credential descriptions for the Credential Engine Registry is to use the ceterms:OrganizationType vocabulary. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/agentType/json

objectProperties.name: aggregateData
objectProperties.annotation: Aggregate Data - vs:stable - Statistical information about the resource. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/aggregateData/json

objectProperties.name: alignmentDate
objectProperties.annotation: Alignment Date - vs:stable - The date  the alignment was made. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/alignmentDate/json

objectProperties.name: alignmentType
objectProperties.annotation: Alignment Type - vs:stable - Type of relationship between two entities. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/alignmentType/json

objectProperties.name: alternateName
objectProperties.annotation: Alternate Name - vs:stable - Alias for the entity including acronyms, alpha-numeric notations, and other forms of name abbreviations in common use such as PhD, MA, and BA. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/alternateName/json

objectProperties.name: alternativeCondition
objectProperties.annotation: Alternative Condition - vs:stable - Constraints, prerequisites, entry conditions, or requirements in a context where more than one alternative condition or path has been defined and from which any one path fulfills the parent condition. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/alternativeCondition/json

objectProperties.name: appealProcess
objectProperties.annotation: Appeal Process - vs:stable - Description of a formal process for objecting to decisions of an organization. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/appealProcess/json

objectProperties.name: approvedIn
objectProperties.annotation: Approved In - vs:stable - Region or political jurisdiction such as a state, province or locale in which an organization pronounces favorable judgment for this credential, assessment, learning opportunity, or organization. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/approvedIn/json

objectProperties.name: assessmentDeliveryType
objectProperties.annotation: Assessment Delivery Type - vs:stable - Delivery type for the assessment for the credential. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/assessmentDeliveryType/json

objectProperties.name: assessmentExample
objectProperties.annotation: Assessment Example - vs:stable - Example assessment or assessment item. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/assessmentExample/json

objectProperties.name: assessmentExampleDescription
objectProperties.annotation: Assessment Example Description - vs:stable - Text of an example assessment or assessment item. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/assessmentExampleDescription/json

objectProperties.name: assessmentMethodDescription
objectProperties.annotation: Assessment Method Description - vs:stable - Description of the methods used to conduct assessment. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/assessmentMethodDescription/json

objectProperties.name: assessmentMethodType
objectProperties.annotation: Assessment Method Type - vs:stable - Type of method used to conduct an assessment; select from an existing enumeration of such types. - Usage Node: Best practice for developing credential descriptions for the Credential Engine Registry is to use the ceterms:AssessmentMethod vocabulary. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/assessmentMethodType/json

objectProperties.name: assessmentOutput
objectProperties.annotation: Assessment Output - vs:stable - Description of the assessment artifact, performance or examination. - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/ceterms/assessmentOutput/json

objectProperties.name: assessmentUseType

concepts.name: Artifact

concepts.name: Performance
concepts.annotation: Performance - vs:stable - Set of behaviors or actions assessed as demonstration of competencies where the assessment occurs either as the actions take place (i.e., live) or through review of recordings of those actions in a persistent media (e.g., video, audio, keystroke records, etc.) - Performance includes, but is not limited to, dance, music, teaching, acting, medical procedures, truck driving, manufacturing production, etc. Criteria include the categories and benchmarks on which the performance is assessed. Methods of evaluation can include multiple evaluators either individually or as an expert panel using general criteria or more structured rubrics whose scores are combined (e.g., assessing a dance performance, evaluating the performance of a medical procedure, truck driving procedure, manufacturing process such as machining). - Change history: http://credreg.net/ctdl/termhistory/assessMethod/Performance/json
